00:58:30.470 --> 00:58:31.695
And it was all political.

00:58:31.695 --> 00:58:33.690
We could have had a question on soccer.

00:58:33.690 --> 00:58:35.706
I thought there'd be one,
but there wasn't.

00:58:35.706 --> 00:58:38.793
- Ask a question about soccer.

00:58:38.793 --> 00:58:39.495
Yeah.

00:58:39.495 --> 00:58:41.738
- OK, soccer then.
- I have a question about that.

00:58:41.738 --> 00:58:42.738
Go ahead.

00:58:42.738 --> 00:58:45.160
Although, I'm not really into soccer.
That's OK.

00:58:45.160 --> 00:58:48.795
- Me neither,
- What's it like to...

00:58:48.795 --> 00:58:52.795
...to score a goal in the World Cup?

00:58:52.795 --> 00:58:55.220
Against Croatia.
What did you feel in that moment?

00:58:55.220 --> 00:58:57.807
Well, to tell the truth,

00:58:58.779 --> 00:59:02.024
I think I was in a daze.

00:59:02.024 --> 00:59:03.804
No, it's true.
Because I think

00:59:03.804 --> 00:59:05.206
what people noticed

00:59:05.206 --> 00:59:07.374
when I was on my knees and all that,

00:59:07.374 --> 00:59:08.762
I think people were saying

00:59:08.762 --> 00:59:11.661
"Hey, this guy doesn't know
what's going on, he looks lost."

00:59:11.661 --> 00:59:13.970
That was the reality of it.

00:59:13.970 --> 00:59:18.732
But, actually, what's really interesting,
when I talk about soccer,

00:59:18.732 --> 00:59:21.222
especially to very young people,

00:59:21.222 --> 00:59:24.022
is telling them that
it's important to have dreams.

00:59:24.022 --> 00:59:25.558
It's really important.

00:59:25.558 --> 00:59:27.950
And you can't achieve them on your own.

00:59:27.950 --> 00:59:30.408
That's why I talk about self-esteem

00:59:30.408 --> 00:59:32.918
and learning that 
you are allowed to make mistakes.

00:59:32.918 --> 00:59:36.237
And that you improve by making mistakes.

00:59:36.237 --> 00:59:38.107
I know this is an American company

00:59:38.107 --> 00:59:41.054
it's partly the culture: in 
France, you can't make mistakes.

00:59:41.054 --> 00:59:44.405
Because otherwise, and I think this is
what we need to encourage...

00:59:44.405 --> 00:59:47.175
we need to tell children,
not to be afraid to make mistakes

00:59:47.175 --> 00:59:49.221
because that's how you progress.

00:59:49.221 --> 00:59:51.701
And most importantly,
you can't succeed on your own.

00:59:51.701 --> 00:59:55.684
Because they tried
portray me as a superhero

00:59:55.684 --> 00:59:58.911
when I scored, but it's quite the opposite

00:59:58.911 --> 01:00:01.733
you don't win matches on your own,
it's not possible. There.

01:00:01.733 --> 01:00:04.533
